  "prompt": "Can we swallow fenugreek seeds as a whole?",
  "response": "Swallowing fenugreek seeds whole is not typically recommended. Fenugreek seeds are hard and can be difficult to digest. It's generally more beneficial to soak or grind them before consumption to aid in digestion and maximize their nutritional benefits. Soaking fenugreek seeds in water overnight makes them softer and easier to swallow, and grinding them into powder can be a useful way to incorporate them into food or beverages. However, if you have any concerns or specific health conditions, it is advisable to consult with a healthcare professional before consuming fenugreek seeds.",
